                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 702.6211/227.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">German Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to inform
                    your excellency that I propose provisionally to place Imperial Consul General
                    Zoepffel, at Atlanta, Georgia, in charge of the Imperial Consulate at Seattle,
                    Washington, and to send Consul Mueller, Acting Consul at Seattle, to Atlanta,
                    there to take charge of the Imperial Consulate.</p>
                <p>I have to ask that you most kindly take the necessary steps to let Consul General
                    Zoepffel and Consul Müller discharge their duties as acting Consuls at Seattle
                    and Atlanta respectively.</p>
                <p>Looking forward to an obliging communication from your excellency so that I may
                    take the necessary action.</p>
                <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Bernstorff</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
